---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy — Fact Attack | Bechard Tech Solutions"
	description="Privacy Policy for the Fact Attack mobile application by Bechard Tech Solutions."
>
	<!-- Minimal Header -->
	<header class="pp-header">
		<div class="pp-header-container">
			<a href="/" class="pp-logo">
				<span class="logo-bracket">&lt;</span>BTS<span class="logo-bracket">/&gt;</span>
			</a>
		</div>
	</header>

	<!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
	<main class="pp-main">
		<div class="pp-container">
			<div class="pp-hero">
				<span class="pp-tag">Legal</span>
				<h1 class="pp-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
				<p class="pp-app-name">Fact Attack</p>
				<p class="pp-effective">Effective date: March 20, 2026</p>
			</div>

			<article class="pp-content">
				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
					<p>
						Welcome to <strong>Fact Attack</strong> (the "App"), developed and operated by
						<strong>Bechard Tech Solutions</strong> ("we", "us", or "our"). This Privacy Policy
						explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use
						our mobile application. Please read this policy carefully. By using the App, you
						agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

					<h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
					<p>We may collect information that you voluntarily provide when using the App, such as:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Username or display name (if applicable)</li>
						<li>Email address (if you contact us or create an account via Email Login)</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>2.2 Authentication Data</h3>
					<p>
						The App supports multiple sign-in methods: <strong>Firebase Anonymous Authentication</strong>,
						<strong>Google Sign-In</strong>, and <strong>Email Login</strong>. If you choose to
						link a third-party account (such as Google), we may receive basic profile information
						from that provider, including your name, email address, and profile picture. This
						information is used solely to personalize your experience within the App.
					</p>

					<h3>2.3 Rewarded Survey Data</h3>
					<p>
						The App offers <strong>Rewarded Surveys</strong> that allow you to earn in-app rewards
						(such as a second guess or a Streak Saver) in exchange for completing short surveys
						provided by third-party survey partners. These surveys may collect demographic
						information, preferences, or opinions. This data is collected directly by the survey
						provider and is subject to their own privacy policy (see Section 4).
					</p>

					<h3>2.4 In-App Search Queries</h3>
					<p>
						The App features a "Know More" button that opens an in-app browser to perform a web
						search related to the current question. These search queries are processed directly
						by the search engine within the in-app browser. <strong>We do not collect, store, or
						track</strong> the specific search queries you perform through this feature.
					</p>

					<h3>2.5 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
					<p>When you use the App, certain information may be collected automatically, including:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Device type, operating system, and version</li>
						<li>Unique device identifiers</li>
						<li>App usage data and interaction statistics</li>
						<li>Crash reports and performance data</li>
						<li>IP address and general location (country/region level)</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
					<p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>To provide, operate, and maintain the App</li>
						<li>To improve, personalize, and expand the App's features</li>
						<li>To understand and analyze how you use the App</li>
						<li>To communicate with you, including for customer support</li>
						<li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues</li>
						<li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
					<p>
						The App uses third-party services that may collect information to identify you.
						These services have their own privacy policies governing the use of your data.
						The third-party service providers we use include:
					</p>

					<h3>4.1 Analytics &amp; Monitoring</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google Analytics for Firebase</strong> — for app usage analytics</li>
						<li><strong>Firebase Crashlytics</strong> — for crash reporting and monitoring</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.2 Advertising</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Google AdMob</strong> — for serving advertisements</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.3 Authentication</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Firebase Authentication</strong> — for anonymous and email-based sign-in</li>
						<li><strong>Google Sign-In</strong> — for account linking and social login (may share your name, email, and profile picture)</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.4 Rewarded Surveys</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Third-party survey providers</strong> — to deliver rewarded surveys that may collect demographic or preference data directly from you. The specific survey provider may vary and will be identified within the App before you participate.</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.5 Payments</h3>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Apple App Store / Google Play Store</strong> — all in-app purchases and subscriptions are processed through the respective platform's payment system (see Section 5)</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.6 AI &amp; Content Generation (Future)</h3>
					<p>
						We may integrate third-party AI or Large Language Model (LLM) providers in the
						future to generate quiz content and provide contextual feedback (see Section 6).
						If and when such providers are integrated, this section will be updated with the
						specific provider name and a link to their privacy policy.
					</p>

					<p>
						We encourage you to review the privacy policies of these third-party providers to
						understand how they process your data.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>5. In-App Purchases &amp; Subscriptions</h2>
					<p>
						The App offers in-app purchases, including a one-time "Remove Ads" option and
						an annual subscription for premium features. All payment transactions are
						processed entirely by the <strong>Apple App Store</strong> or <strong>Google Play
						Store</strong>, depending on your device platform.
					</p>
					<p>
						<strong>We do not collect, store, or have access to your credit card details,
						banking information, or any other financial data.</strong> All payment processing,
						refunds, and subscription management are handled directly by Apple or Google. We
						only receive a confirmation of purchase status to unlock the corresponding features
						within the App.
					</p>
					<p>
						For information about how your payment data is handled, please refer to the privacy
						policies of <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google</a>
						or <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple</a>.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>6. AI-Generated Content (Future)</h2>
					<p>
						We plan to integrate third-party <strong>Large Language Model (LLM)</strong> providers
						in the future to generate quiz questions, provide contextual feedback, and support
						hyper-specific topic requests. When this feature is implemented:
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Your topic selections or custom requests may be sent to an external AI provider to generate relevant content</li>
						<li>We will not send any personally identifiable information to the AI provider</li>
						<li>This policy will be updated to identify the specific AI provider and link to their privacy policy before the feature is released</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>7. Data Storage &amp; Security</h2>
					<p>
						We value your trust in providing us your information and strive to use commercially
						acceptable means of protecting it. However, no method of transmission over the
						internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee
						its absolute security.
					</p>
					<p>
						Your data may be stored and processed on servers located outside your country of
						residence. By using the App, you consent to the transfer of your information to
						these locations.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
					<p>
						The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not
						knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover that
						a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will promptly delete
						it. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with
						personal data, please contact us.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
					<p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>The right to access the personal data we hold about you</li>
						<li>The right to request correction of inaccurate data</li>
						<li>The right to request deletion of your personal data</li>
						<li>The right to withdraw consent at any time</li>
						<li>The right to data portability</li>
					</ul>
					<p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
					<p>
						We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any
						changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Effective
						date" at the top. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for
						any changes. Changes are effective when they are posted on this page.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="pp-section">
					<h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
					<p>
						If you have any questions or suggestions about this Privacy Policy, do not
						hesitate to contact us:
					</p>
					<div class="pp-contact">
						<a href="mailto:contact@bechardtechsolutions.com" class="pp-contact-link">
							<svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="20" height="16" x="2" y="4" rx="2"/><path d="m22 7-8.97 5.7a1.94 1.94 0 0 1-2.06 0L2 7"/></svg>
							contact@bechardtechsolutions.com
						</a>
					</div>
				</section>
			</article>
		</div>
	</main>

	<!-- Minimal Footer -->
	<footer class="pp-footer">
		<div class="pp-container">
			<p>&copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} Bechard Tech Solutions. All rights reserved.</p>
		</div>
	</footer>
</Layout>

<style>
	/* ===== HEADER ===== */
	.pp-header {
		position: fixed;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		z-index: 1000;
		padding: 1rem 2rem;
		background: rgba(10, 10, 26, 0.85);
		backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.pp-header-container {
		max-width: var(--container-max);
		margin: 0 auto;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.pp-logo {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--color-text);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		transition: opacity var(--transition-fast);
	}

	.pp-logo:hover {
		opacity: 0.8;
	}

	.logo-bracket {
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	/* ===== MAIN CONTENT ===== */
	.pp-main {
		padding-top: 6rem;
		padding-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.pp-container {
		max-width: 780px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 2rem;
	}

	/* ===== HERO ===== */
	.pp-hero {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
		padding-bottom: 3rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
	}

	.pp-tag {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--color-primary-light);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.15em;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.pp-title {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-gradient-start), var(--color-gradient-end));
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pp-app-name {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.pp-effective {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: var(--color-text-subtle);
	}

	/* ===== ARTICLE CONTENT ===== */
	.pp-content {
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	.pp-section {
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}

	.pp-section h2 {
		font-size: 1.35rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.pp-section h3 {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.pp-section p {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.pp-section ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.pp-section li {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		padding: 0.35rem 0 0.35rem 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
	}

	.pp-section li::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		top: 50%;
		transform: translateY(-50%);
		width: 6px;
		height: 6px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--color-primary);
	}

	.pp-section strong {
		color: var(--color-text);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	/* ===== CONTACT ===== */
	.pp-contact {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.pp-contact-link {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
		background: var(--color-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		border-radius: var(--radius-md);
		color: var(--color-primary-light);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: all var(--transition-fast);
	}

	.pp-contact-link:hover {
		border-color: var(--color-border-hover);
		background: var(--color-surface-hover);
		transform: translateY(-1px);
		box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.1);
	}

	/* ===== FOOTER ===== */
	.pp-footer {
		border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
		padding: 2rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.pp-footer p {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--color-text-subtle);
	}

	/* ===== RESPONSIVE ===== */
	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.pp-main {
			padding-top: 5rem;
		}

		.pp-hero {
			margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
			padding-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		.pp-section {
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		.pp-contact-link {
			font-size: 0.85rem;
			padding: 0.6rem 1.2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
